The paper discusses the use of Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks, a type of Recurrent Neural Network (RNN), for anomaly detection in spacecraft telemetry data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of developing and maintaining anomaly detection systems, which suggests that it may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper focuses on the application of anomaly detection to spacecraft monitoring, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
